pdp_descriptions: The Koldfront 10,600 BTU 208/230V Through the Wall Air Conditioner (WTC10001W) is the ideal choice for keeping your home comfortable during warm summer months. As a through the wall unit, the WTC10001W will provide efficient cooling to the room of your choice without taking up window space or protruding from the outside of your home. Because the unit remains mounted on a wall inside your home, you will only have to install it once without worrying about storing the unit during harsh winter conditions. The user-friendly control panel with a digital display makes it easy to control a wide array of settings, including temperature, fan speeds, and programmable timer operations. Three (3) fan speeds have a measurement of 253, 275, and 293 CFM’s. When it comes to convenient home cooling, you can't go wrong with the WTC10001W through the wall air conditioner. A sleeve must be purchased for proper installation and is not included with the unit. Set sleep mode before going to bed, and the unit will automatically increase the temperature in small increments, and then return to it’s original set temperature after 6 hours, allowing you to save energy overnight and wake up just as comfortable as ever. The air conditioner's installation requires the WTCSLV wall sleeve (not included), which forms a tight seal between the unit and the wall, allowing cool air to stay sealed inside, while the warm air that is exhausted outside cannot reenter your home. Another advantage to the wall mounted installation is that it does not require you to sacrifice access to a window or the view from it. The unit utilizes R-410A refrigerant which is an eco-friendly refrigerant of the future, and has recently be recognized by the EPA for not having bromine or chlorine, and consequently will not harm or deplete the ozone. The unit includes an easy to clean air filter that ensures only clean and fresh air will be circulated throughout your home. Dimensions: 20-3/8" D x 14-1/2" H x 24-1/4" W

pdp_descriptions: The LG Packaged Terminal Air Conditioner PTAC, is a self-contained heating and air conditioning system commonly found in hotels, motels, senior housing facilities, hospitals, condominiums, apartment buildings, add-on rooms & sunrooms. User-Friendly Display All of the operations can be handled from the convenient display on the unit. Operation mode, fan speed, temperature, and timer functions are easily set through the control panel's push buttons. Energy Saving Mode When energy saving mode is active, the unit's fan will only run during cooling or heating operations. This prevents continuous fan use which drains energy without affecting the temperature. Long Lasting Filters LG PTAC units don't just control the temperature, they also clean the air that flows through them. This unit's air filters and vent filter are washable, making it easy to ensure that your guests enjoy ideal air quality. Quiet Comfort The LG PTACs employ a split motor configuration that shifts the noisier operations to an outdoor motor. Both the indoor and outdoor motors are brushless direct current motors, which are renowned for their low levels of electrical and mechanical noise. Gold Fin Protection The corrosive effects of outside air can damage a PTAC and drastically reduce the lifespan of the unit. LG's PTAC units are treated with their Gold Fin corrosion-inhibiting coating to improve their longevity and durability. Multiple Thermostat Options Each LG PTAC comes with a thermostat connection kit allowing you to use a thermostat of your choosing. LG also offers wireless and wired remote options that have easy-to-use digital displays and will control all of your PTAC's functions.

pdp_descriptions: The Kooltronic KA4C4NP33L, one of our TrimLine Series indoor/outdoor Enclosure Air Conditioners. Innovations in technology have resulted in much denser components packaging and smaller available panel sizes on which to mount air conditioners. The KOOLTRONIC TrimLine Enclosure Air Conditioner Series is the response to these new packaging demands with Narrow 10", 12", 15" and 17" width panel-mount air conditioners. In addition to being narrower than traditional air conditioner units, the TrimLine Series include the Condensate Evaporator and Low Temperature Control Thermostat as standard features and are available in all popular voltages and frequencies. The NP17, NP28, NP33 and Narrow-Mini models feature a Programmable Thermostat as a standard feature. The TrimLine Series Enclosure Air Conditioner consists of two series of compact models, the NP Series and the NPT Series. The NP Series models offer capacities from 2,000 to 7,000 BTU/H and use CFC-Free R134a refrigerant. The NPT Series offers units with capacities from 4,000 to 16,000 BTU/H and use Zero Ozone Depleting R410a refrigerant. The TrimLine Series consists of models rated for NEMA 12 and NEMA 3R. Please check specifications for individual model approvals. Please inquire with the manufacturer about quantity discounts. This enclosure cooling model is the perfect choice for virtually every application such as kiosk, medical, wastewater, food and beverage and telecommunications. Kooltronic has been manufacturing enclosure thermal management products since 1956 and is located in Pennington, NJ.

IMPORTANT: To ensure the proper functioning of your new air conditioner, please allow the unit to stand in an upright for position for at least 24 hours before operating. Although we remind our shipping partners about the importance of keeping these units in their upright position, mistakes happen, and units may be shipped in improper positions. If you do not sit your unit in the upright position for 24 hours before operation, this will seriously affect the capability of the compressor and ultimately the production of cold air.
